PyQuery is a simple tool to parse/query bad html in a simple way 
directly from the Commandline. Its written in Python and does work on 
python 2.5 -2.6 and u need Beautifullsoup 
installed.(http://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/)

License: BSD (see source) 


++Short Tutorial++

Download pyquery.py and Beautifullsoup(install). Put pyquery in any 
directory, make it executable with """ # chmod +x pyquery.py """ and 
then fire it """ ./pyquery.py --help """ to see availabel options. Then 
feed in HTML through stdin (pipes) """ cat some.html | ./pyquery.py -t 
div """ and watch the magic ;)
